        "id": "72f5f68e688ef75dbd3c637a5ba29a08bb721f4f",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 87,
          "name": "Dan Timoney",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "dtimoney@att.com",
          "username": "djtimoney"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2017-06-22 12:47:50.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 4: Code-Review-2\n\nThe features pom.xml itself should have the repo's pom.xml as its parent - not features-parent.  What we really should do is create a new project parent (like rootpom/pom.xml) whose parent is feature-parent vs odlparent.  I'm asking to move the rootpom from sdnc/core to a separate repo (sdnc/parent) to resolve current circular dependency.  Once that is created, we'll have multiple parent poms defined in that new project so that projects that build features can use features-parent as ancestor.",
        "patchset_number": 4
      },
